      <section eId="sec_603">
        <num>603</num>
        <heading>Separate tax on the ordinary income portion of lump sum distributions</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_603__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Imposition of separate tax. In addition to any other\ntax imposed by this article, there is hereby imposed for each taxable\nyear a separate tax on the ordinary income portion of a lump sum\ndistribution of every individual, estate and trust which has made an\nelection of lump sum treatment under subsection</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_603__subsec_e">
          <num>(e)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of section four\nhundred two of the internal revenue code. The recipient of a lump sum\ndistribution shall be liable for the tax imposed by this section. The\ncredits against tax under this article, except for the credits under\nparagraphs two and four of subsection</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_603__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>, paragraphs two and four of\nsubsection</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_603__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>and subsection</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_603__subsec_e">
          <num>(e)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of section six hundred six, section\nsix hundred twenty-A and section six hundred seventy-three, shall not be\nallowed against the tax imposed by this section.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_603__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Cross reference. For computation of tax, see section six hundred\ntwenty-four with respect to residents and section six hundred\nthirty-seven with respect to nonresidents and part-year residents.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
